comments.body:
I hacked together a patch to assign the correct owner and permissions to the volume folder (@rhatdan approach is maybe better).

With this patch write access works for the mysql user but now I can actually fall in the bug as originally reported, that is the start command following a stop does not remount the volume correctly.


After the start, an  ```ls -ls /var/lib/mysql/data```  from inside the container gives the following:
```0 drwx------ 1 root root 92 Jun 14 15:38 data```

And by checking inside the ```data``` folder (as root user), I see that something is definitely wrong:
```# ls /var/lib/mysql/data/
artifacts  attach  config.json  ctl  ctr.log  shm  volumes
```
Also there seems to be an extra mount point that should not be there:
```
# mount
...
shm on /var/lib/mysql/data/shm type tmpfs (rw,nosuid,nodev,noexec,relatime,size=64000k)
...
```

Finally here's the patch I mentioned before:

```diff
diff --git a/libpod/container_internal.go b/libpod/container_internal.go
index f6d8fc3..f15cb6a 100644
--- a/libpod/container_internal.go
+++ b/libpod/container_internal.go
@@ -1324,6 +1324,21 @@ func (c *Container) addImageVolumes(ctx context.Context, g *generate.Generator)
 			if err = os.MkdirAll(volumePath, 0755); err != nil {
 				return errors.Wrapf(err, "error creating directory %q for volume %q in container %q", volumePath, k, c.ID)
 			}
+
+			if c.config.User != "" {
+				if !c.state.Mounted {
+					return errors.Wrapf(ErrCtrStateInvalid, "container %s must be mounted in order to translate User field", c.ID())
+				}
+				uid, gid, err := chrootuser.GetUser(c.state.Mountpoint, c.config.User)
+				if err != nil {
+					return err
+				}
+
+				if err = os.Chown(volumePath, int(uid), int(gid)); err != nil {
+					return errors.Wrapf(err, "error chowning directory %q for volume %q in container %q", volumePath, k, c.ID)
+				}
+			}
+
 			if err = label.Relabel(volumePath, c.config.MountLabel, false); err != nil {
 				return errors.Wrapf(err, "error relabeling directory %q for volume %q in container %q", volumePath, k, c.ID)
 			}
```
